Text: FW Chris DorlandPST Original Message From Becky Gilfry ENRON Sent Thursday January PM To Pechersky Julie Cc Rondeau Clayton Subject RE Chris Dorland Julie My apologiesit was on delayed but not any longer Becky Original Message From Pechersky Julie mailto Sent Thursday January AM To Cc Rondeau Clayton Subject Chris Dorland Becky Clayton in the Calgary office called and said that Chris Dorland seems to be receiving NYMEX quotes delayedis he permissioned for that exchange real time Thanks julie This email is the property of Enron Corp andor its relevant affiliate and may contain confidential and privileged material for the sole use of the intended recipient s Any review use distribution or disclosure by others is strictly prohibited If you are not the intended recipient or authorized to receive for the recipient please contact the sender or reply to Enron Corp at and delete all copies of the message This email and any attachments hereto are not intended to be an offer or an acceptance and do not create or evidence a binding and enforceable contract between Enron Corp or any of its affiliates and the intended recipient or any other party and may not be relied on by anyone as the basis of a contract by estoppel or otherwise Thank you

FW Chris DorlandPST Original Message From Pechersky Julie Sent Thursday January AM To Cc Rondeau Clayton Subject Chris Dorland Becky Clayton in the Calgary office called and said that Chris Dorland seems to be receiving NYMEX quotes delayedis he permissioned for that exchange real time Thanks julie

From Garrett TrippForwarded by Clayton RondeauCALECT on PM From Stephane Brodeur on PM EST To Clayton CT cc Subject Ontario Supply and Demand Appendices Update Forwarded by Stephane BrodeurTORECT on PM Garrett Tripp PM To Stephane CT cc Subject Ontario Supply and Demand Appendices Update Forwarded by Garrett TrippTORECT on PM Garrett Tripp PM To cc Subject Ontario Supply and Demand Appendices Update John I have attached some updated appendices from last Mays Ontario Electricity Supply Demand report created by Eric LeDain Unfortunately the IMO has not updated the Monthly Generation by Type Monthly Imports Exports by Intertie and the Nuclear Performance Reports In early November we had requested all IMO Transition Information be updated To date the IMO has only updated hourly demand information As we continue to pressure the IMO more information will be available Updates were made on the following appendices Ontario Net ExportsImports January through August of Scatter Diagram of Load and Cooling Degree Days Ontario Average Peak Demand at each Temperature and through the month of October Peak Supply and Demand I would like to submit a complete report when the IMO Transition Information is updated Toronto is great We have a quality team here Im am anxious for the market to open Garrett
